Where is the market going - a constant question asked by Fin TV moderators. I watch in amazement "talking heads" precision of forecast in response. I try not to talk with precision about my market forecast. A forecast to me is not a point/level - its a reflection of

probabilities of scenarios. The investment mosaic is complicated and ever changing -- though many want one simple (and it is!) answer to the above. The pros I listen to @revshark @Sarge986 @hemeisler don't talk in precision they write about trend and make broader observations

not encapsulated in a market price target. It pays to pay attention to them and not the self confident and non rigorous Fugazzis who make it seem easy. It is not easy @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @riskreversal @guyadami @terranovajoe @beckyquick

I certainly dont have all the answers and I am frequently wrong. But I am transparent in view/analysis and actions on @realmoney @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @CNBCFastMoney And I take ownership of my mistakes.
